sleNetwork6.name: sleNetwork6
sleNetwork6.description: This MIB contains information about Network6.

sleNdPrefixDefault.name: sleNdPrefixDefault
sleNdPrefixDefault.description: If default flag is set, prefix value and mask have no mean.

sleNdPrefixOffLink.name: sleNdPrefixOffLink
sleNdPrefixOffLink.description: Use or do not use prefix for onlink determination

sleNdPrefixNoAutoconfig.name: sleNdPrefixNoAutoconfig
sleNdPrefixNoAutoconfig.description: Use or do not use prefix for autoconfiguration

sleNeighbour6Address.name: sleNeighbour6Address
sleNeighbour6Address.description: The IP6Address corresponding to the media-dependent `physical' address.

sleNeighbour6PortIndex.name: sleNeighbour6PortIndex
sleNeighbour6PortIndex.description: The interface on which this entry's equivalence is effective. 0: for any ports. (if sleNeighbour6HwUsed is 0, always 0)

sleNeighbour6HwUsed.name: sleNeighbour6HwUsed
sleNeighbour6HwUsed.description: Neighbour6 entry's currently chip usage state.

sleRoute6DstAddress.name: sleRoute6DstAddress
sleRoute6DstAddress.description: The destination IP6 address of this route. Multiple routes to a single destination can appear in the table, but access to such multiple entries is dependent on the table-access mechanisms defined by the network management protocol in use.

sleRoute6DstMask.name: sleRoute6DstMask
sleRoute6DstMask.description: Indicate the mask to be logical-ANDed with the destination address before being compared to the value in the sleRoute6DstAddress field.

sleRoute6Proto.name: sleRoute6Proto
sleRoute6Proto.description: The routing mechanism via which this route was learned. Inclusion of values for gateway routing protocols is not intended to imply that hosts should support those protocols. other - not specified local - local interface netmgmt - static route icmp - result of ICMP Redirect egp - Exterior Gateway Protocol ggp - Gateway-Gateway Protocol hello - FuzzBall HelloSpeak rip - Berkeley RIP or RIP-II is-is - Dual IS-IS es-is - ISO 9542 ciscoIgrp - Cisco IGRP bbnSpfIgp - BBN SPF IGP ospf - Open Shortest Path First bgp - Border Gateway Protocol idpr - InterDomain Policy Routing ciscoEigrp - Cisco EIGRP

sleRoute6Gateway.name: sleRoute6Gateway
sleRoute6Gateway.description: The Gateway IP 6 Address. ::0 : indicate invalid

sleRoute6Type.name: sleRoute6Type
sleRoute6Type.description: The type of route. Note that the values direct and indirect refer to the notion of direct and indirect routing in the IP architecture.

sleRoute6Distance.name: sleRoute6Distance
sleRoute6Distance.description: The Distance value for this route.

sleRoute6Metric.name: sleRoute6Metric
sleRoute6Metric.description: The primary routing metric for this route. The semantics of this metric are determined by the routing-protocol specified in the route's sleRoute6Proto value. If this metric is not used, its value should be set to -1.

sleRoute6Active.name: sleRoute6Active
sleRoute6Active.description: The active status for this routing entry.

sleRoute6NexthopStatus.name: sleRoute6NexthopStatus
sleRoute6NexthopStatus.description: The nexthop status of this route.

sleRoute6RibStatus.name: sleRoute6RibStatus
sleRoute6RibStatus.description: The rib status for this route.
